---
import LegalLayout from '~/layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { BRAND_NAME } from '~/data/site';
---

<LegalLayout routeKey="responsibleGambling">
  <p>
    Gambling is supposed to be fun. If it stops being fun, stop. {BRAND_NAME}
    is committed to honest, transparent coverage that helps you make informed
    choices - and that includes the choice to take a break or quit.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Free, confidential help (24/7)</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>National Gambling Helpline (UK)</strong> - 0808 8020 133. Free,
      24-hour, confidential.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>BeGambleAware.org</strong> - online self-help, live chat and
      directory of free counsellors.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>National Council on Problem Gambling (US)</strong> -
      1-800-GAMBLER. 24-hour, multilingual.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>GamCare</strong> - online forum, live chat, in-person and group
      treatment.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Gamblers Anonymous</strong> - peer-led 12-step program with daily
      meetings worldwide.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Self-assessment - the 9-question screen</h2>
  <p>If you answer "yes" to two or more of the following, please reach out for help:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Have you needed to bet larger amounts to feel the same excitement?</li>
    <li>Have you been restless or irritable when trying to cut back?</li>
    <li>Have you tried to stop and failed?</li>
    <li>Are you preoccupied with gambling?</li>
    <li>Do you gamble to escape problems or relieve depression?</li>
    <li>Do you chase losses (return to win it back)?</li>
    <li>Have you lied about how much you gamble?</li>
    <li>Have you committed an illegal act to fund gambling?</li>
    <li>Has gambling damaged a relationship, job or education?</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>3. Set deposit limits</h2>
  <p>
    Every operator we cover lets you set daily, weekly and monthly deposit
    limits in the account settings. Set them <strong>before</strong> you start a
    session, not after.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Self-exclusion at every operator we cover</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Stake</strong> - permanent self-exclusion via support@stake.com.</li>
    <li><strong>Roobet</strong> - cooling-off, time-out and permanent options in account settings.</li>
    <li><strong>Rainbet</strong> - 24h, 7d, 30d, 6m and permanent self-exclusion.</li>
    <li><strong>Shuffle</strong> - reality checks, deposit limits and permanent self-exclusion.</li>
    <li><strong>BC.Game</strong> - 24h to lifetime exclusion via support ticket.</li>
    <li><strong>Cloudbet</strong> - permanent self-exclusion via account settings.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Block gambling sites at the device level</h2>
  <p>
    Tools such as <strong>GAMSTOP</strong> (UK), <strong>Gamban</strong>,
    <strong>BetBlocker</strong> and <strong>Net Nanny</strong> block known
    gambling URLs at the device or DNS level. They are free or low-cost and
    work even on devices the operator cannot reach.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Talk to someone</h2>
  <p>
    The National Gambling Helpline (UK 0808 8020 133) and the National Council
    on Problem Gambling helpline (US 1-800-GAMBLER) are free, confidential and
    open 24/7. Trained counsellors will not judge you and will not push you
    into a treatment programme you do not want.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
